<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n14222e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14222e">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14222e"> 222(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> figliuo di Dio Seth / &dash; e d&apos;uomini Cain</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Cos&igrave; si fanno veri i Giganti: de&apos; quali la <i>sacra storia</i> n&agrave;rra che nacquero <i>dalla confusione de&apos; semi umani de&apos; <mark>figliuoli di Dio</mark></i>, che <i>Samuele Bocarto</i> spiega, de&apos; <i>discendenti di Seto</i> innanzi, e noi suplimmo di <i>Semo</i> dopo il diluvio, con <i><mark>le figliuole degli uomini</mark></i>, che&apos;l <i>Bocarto</i> spiega con la <i>discendeza di <mark>Caino</mark></i> innanzi, e noi anche con quella di <i>Cam e Giafet</i> dopo il diluvio: narra che i Giganti furono <i>uomini forti famosi del secolo</i>: e narrando altres&igrave; che <i>Caino fu il fondatore delle citt&agrave;</i> avanti, e <i>Nembrot</i> gigante innalza la gran torre dopo il diluvio<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <br><cite>Vico The First New Science</cite> 71-2: Thus the giants become true. Sacred history relates that they were born of the confusion of the human seed of the sons of God with the daughters of men.<sup>74</sup> According to Samuel Bochart these sons of God were the de-scendants of <mark>Seth</mark> and the daughters of men were the descendants of <mark>Cain</mark>, all living before the Flood. But to the sons of God we would add the descendants of Shem and to the daughters of men those of Ham and Japhet, all living after the Flood. Sacred history de-scribes these giants as &lsquo;the famous strong men of their <font color="green">[71]</font> age&rsquo;, and goes on to relate that Cain founded cities before the Flood and that the giant Nimrod erected the great tower <font color="green">[of Ba-bel]</font> after it. <br>71n74: Genesis, 6:4. <small> Giambattista Vico, <a name="VICO1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VICO1"><cite title="source">Principj di una Scienza Nuova</cite></a> (1836) 87</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: It. <i>Figliuoli di Dio</i>. Sons of God. <i>E d&apos;uomini</i>. And of man. </mm> </dd></dl>
